## Version Format
Public: `major.minor[.build[.revision]]-(alpha|beta|rc)`

## Version Component Definitions

### Major (1)
Architectural paradigm shifts or complete rewrites. Incremented when foundational changes break compatibility.

### Minor (2)
Feature additions, significant improvements, or architectural refinements. Incremented when new capabilities ship.

### Build (0)
Bug fixes, patches, performance optimizations. Incremented for production releases.

### Revision (none)
Critical hotfixes applied after release. Only included if > 0.

### Release Type
- **alpha**: Experimental, early access, API unstable
- **beta**: Feature-complete, some edge cases may exist, primary features stable
- **rc**: Release candidate, production-ready pending final QA

## Migration Path
- Internal versions continue independently
- Public version tracks major releases for user-facing stability
- Subsystems (SENSE, SRE, XSKILL) remain on their own version tracks
